beforeAll: Runs exactly once before any of the tests in the file start executing. It is perfect for heavy setup tasks like launching a database connection, seeding data, or authenticating a global user.

afterAll: Runs exactly once after all the tests in the file have finished executing. It is used for cleanup tasks like closing database connections, deleting temporary test files, or resetting states.


